On Thu, 20 Mar 2003, Blake Haralson wrote:

> Can the torsion bar be adjusted (or mis-adjusted) to the point of
> causing this drastic difference?

Yup.  See the bentley manual.

> If so, shouldn't my bus be handling really bad?

It wouldn't nessecarily be obvious to you.  It's likely to ride a bit
stiff in the rear and could possibly "top" out when bouncing around on
rough roads. (that is, when bouncing up it could hit travel limits.)


